text: Trine Gjesti Bentzen (born 3 July 1973) is a Norwegian sport wrestler. She won a bronze medal at the 1990 World Wrestling Championships in Luleå. She placed fourth in the 50 kg class at the 1993 World Wrestling Championships in Stavern. ==References== Category:1973 births Category:Living people Category:Norwegian female sport wrestlers Category:World Wrestling Championships medalists
